 I need to avoid creating unwanted stubs. Perhaps MethodHandles could help out, too!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Managing test compilation and execution**\\n\\nI’ve been reminded that we shouldn’t compile or run tests ourselves, but I'm already unsure if I can make changes. Could I use MethodHandles after the public path to simplify things and avoid Groovy MetaClass complexity? I'm contemplating whether direct MethodHandles would give a genuine call stack frame. However, if I still have to account for direct reflection methods, I wonder how this might affect the stack trace. It feels like there's a lot to consider!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xY8v3Nx1XkAsVm4IapNjDae1|fc_0c3e80c2c319c20b016a284fdd292c8196947de13ebeab2566", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/JohnzonMapperInner_serialize_closure1Test.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "            assertThat(invokeGeneratedClassLookup(generatedJohnzonClosure.get(), Map.class.getName()))\n                    .isEqualTo(Map.class);\n", "newText": "            assertThat(invokeGeneratedClassLookup(generatedJohnzonClosure.get(), RestAssured.class.getName()))\n                    .isEqualTo(RestAssured.class);\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1272, "output": 1505, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56537, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781026742457, "responseId": "resp_0c3e80c2c319c20b016a284fb700c0819687bd4d3d48312fa6"}}
